about.summary: Utilities for paths, files and directories.

name: r-pathological
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.1-2' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-pathological
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/pathological_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/pathological/pathological_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: c2922252b2eb30a7e484b5c07817696ef99273495af18992472976f78dbee71d

build:
  noarch: generic
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1002
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:

  host:
    - r-base
    - r-assertive.base >=0.0_3
    - r-assertive.files
    - r-assertive.numbers
    - r-assertive.properties
    - r-assertive.reflection
    - r-assertive.strings
    - r-assertive.types
    - r-magrittr
    - r-plyr
    - r-stringi
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-assertive.base >=0.0_3
    - r-assertive.files
    - r-assertive.numbers
    - r-assertive.properties
    - r-assertive.reflection
    - r-assertive.strings
    - r-assertive.types
    - r-magrittr
    - r-plyr
    - r-stringi

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('pathological')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('pathological')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/richierocks/pathological
  license: Unlimited
  summary: Utilities for paths, files and directories.
  license_family: OTHER

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - johanneskoester
    - bgruening
    - daler
    - jdblischak
    - cbrueffer
    - dbast
